# arvo invariants — re-read before every action

These invariants bind every edit in this repo. If an edit conflicts,
stop and reconsider the design before writing code.

- `#![no_std]` in every crate. No `alloc`. No `std::*` imports.
- No `Vec`, `String`, `Box`. Use `[T; N]` or consumer-owned buffers.
- No `dyn`, no `TypeId`, no `std::any`. Monomorphisation IS the
  dispatch.
- Every numeric type with a precision/throughput tradeoff carries
  `S: Strategy = Warm`.
- `arvo-bits` is contracts only: traits with default methods and
  blanket impls. No fielded `pub struct` there.
- Sizes are const. No `.push(`, `.resize(`, `.extend(`. If you need
  "more space", make it a const generic or change the consumer.
- No platform: no `std::thread`, `std::time`, `std::fs`, `std::net`.
- Dependency direction: L0 → L1 → L2 → L3 only. Never back.
- Design before code: if the edit doesn't follow a matching
  `design_rounds/*.src.md` changelist, stop.
- Edit templates under `mock/agent/*.tmpl`, never the generated
  `.claude/` or `.github/` files.
